Change-Id: I8ad77c45e1e9238284a5b69815d2414f446ca783","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/3c333304693686ce640812b56094b6cd19de3749"},{"sha":"b9c4639bc85304eac69d76fd3f1bff02ad5df978","author":{"name":"Smit Hinsu","email":"0f9dce5f2da36d8473ff9a50fbb0e06a148c5fae@google.com"},"message":"Remove incorrect shape inference method for XlaSetDynamicDimensionSizeOp

Currently, the method sets result type to be same as the input type disregarding dim_index and size operands, which is incorrect.

Removing the incorrect shape inference method to begin with. The correct method should have ranked result with unknown dimensions if dim_index is not static and unknown dimension at dim_index if it is static. We should also keep the original size for the dimension as the bound if it was known.
